      h1
        code= config.name
      p
        code iostap
        |  is a plugin designed to mimic the behaviour of tapping a button in
        | the iOS ecosystem with a great degree of precision, affording
        | developers who build hybrid web apps a greater experience for
        | their users.
        |
        code iostap
        |  is a super-lightweight library, weighing in at about 1kb, and
        | doesn't add unecessary overhead client-side.
      p
        | Download the source files from the
        |
        code build
        |  directory, or use
        |
        a(href="http://www.bower.io/") Bower
        | .
      .highlight.highlight-bash
        pre.
          $ bower install iostap
    .column
      h4
        code Active state
      .well
        p.button
          | Button
      p
        | The active state should be removed once the user moves their pointer
        | a significant distance from the button. This cancels the
        code "iostap"
        | event. Bringing the finger back to the button will re-instate the
        | active class.
      p
        pre.
          .button {...}

          // Active styles
          .button.__active {...}
